{"author":{"id":"b78c39e7b13f90a5827abfba043255fe7a4ede1499df23f110fffe5abfa44adc"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1770924494,"nonce":"nrrgWxg6Sz8m3FTcQOTkZuku5EY=","metadata":{"github-id":"I_kwDOQ241x87qditb","github-url":"https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/193","origin":"github"},"title":"worktree_create.sh: layer type incorrectly creates workspace-level git worktree","message":"## Bug\n\n`worktree_create.sh --type layer` unconditionally creates a git worktree from the **workspace root repo** (lines 241-247) before setting up the per-package worktrees. This top-level worktree is only meaningful for `--type workspace` but runs for both types.\n\n### Impact\n\nWhen a workspace worktree already exists for the same issue (e.g., `feature/issue-55` branch is checked out in `.workspace-worktrees/issue-workspace-55`), creating a layer worktree for the same issue fails with:\n\n```\nfatal: 'feature/issue-55' is already used by worktree at\n'/path/to/.workspace-worktrees/issue-workspace-55'\n```\n\nEven without that conflict, the layer worktree creation produces an unnecessary workspace-level worktree directory in addition to the actual per-package worktrees.\n\n### Root Cause\n\nLines 241-247 run unconditionally for both worktree types:\n\n```bash\nif [ \"$BRANCH_EXISTS\" = true ]; then\n    echo \"Using existing branch '$BRANCH_NAME'...\"\n    git worktree add \"$WORKTREE_DIR\" \"$BRANCH_NAME\"\nelse\n    echo \"Creating new branch '$BRANCH_NAME' from current HEAD...\"\n    git worktree add -b \"$BRANCH_NAME\" \"$WORKTREE_DIR\"\nfi\n```\n\nThis executes from `$ROOT_DIR` (the workspace repo), so it creates a worktree in the workspace repo. For `--type layer`, the real worktrees are created later per-package at lines 316-341 using `cd \"$pkg_path\"` to operate on the correct repo.\n\n### Suggested Fix\n\nWrap lines 241-247 in a conditional so they only run for `--type workspace`:\n\n```bash\nif [ \"$WORKTREE_TYPE\" == \"workspace\" ]; then\n    if [ \"$BRANCH_EXISTS\" = true ]; then\n        ...\n    fi\nfi\n```\n\nFor `--type layer`, the parent directory (`$WORKTREE_DIR`) should be created with `mkdir -p` instead of `git worktree add`, since it's just a container for the per-package worktrees and symlinks.\n\n---\n**Authored-By**: `Claude Code Agent`\n**Model**: `Claude Opus 4.6`","files":null}]}